  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David Learns of Saul\u2019s Death"
      title: "David Learns of Saul\u2019s Death"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it happened after the death of Saul, when David had returned
        from the slaughter of the Amalekites, that he stayed two days in Ziklag. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "On the third day a man came [unexpectedly] from Saul\u2019s camp
        with his clothes torn and dust on his head [as in mourning]. When he came
        to David, he bowed to the ground and lay himself face down [in an act of
        great respect and submission]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then David asked him, \u201CWhere do you come from?\u201D He said,
        \u201CI have escaped from the camp of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "David said to him, \u201CHow did it go? Please tell me.\u201D He
        answered, \u201CThe people have fled from the battle. Also, many of the people
        have fallen and are dead; Saul and Jonathan his son are also dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David said to the young man who informed him, \u201CHow do you
        know Saul and his son Jonathan are dead?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the young man who told him explained, \u201CBy chance I happened
        to be on Mount Gilboa, and there was Saul leaning on his spear, and the chariots
        and horsemen [of the Philistines] were close behind him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When he turned to look behind him, he saw me, and called to me. And
        I answered, \u2018Here I am.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "He asked me, \u2018Who are you?\u2019 I answered him, \u2018I am
        an Amalekite.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said to me, \u2018Stand up facing me and kill me, for [terrible]
        agony has come over me, yet I still live [and I will be taken alive].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So I stood facing him and killed him, because I knew that he could
        not live after he had fallen. Then I took the crown which was on his head
        and the band which was on his arm, and I have brought them here to my lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then David grasped his own clothes and tore them [in mourning]; so
        did all the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They mourned and wept and fasted until evening for Saul and Jonathan
        his son, and for the Lord\u2019s people and the house of Israel, because
        they had fallen by the sword [in battle]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "David said to the young man who informed him, \u201CWhere are you
        from?\u201D He answered, \u201CI am the son of a foreigner (resident alien,
        sojourner), an Amalekite.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "David said to him, \u201CHow is it that you were not afraid to put
        out your hand to destroy the Lord\u2019s anointed?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "David called one of the young men and said, \u201CGo, execute him.\u201D
        So he struck the Amalekite and he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: "16: David\u2019s Dirge for Saul and Jonathan"
      title: "David\u2019s Dirge for Saul and Jonathan"
      number: 16
      content: "David said to the [fallen] man, \u201CYour blood is on your own head,
        for your own mouth has testified against you, saying, \u2018I have killed
        the Lord\u2019s anointed.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then David sang this dirge (funeral song) over Saul and his son Jonathan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and he told them to teach the sons of Judah, the song of the bow.
        Behold, it is written in the Book of Jashar:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYour glory and splendor, O Israel, is slain upon your high
        places!How the mighty have fallen!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Tell it not in Gath,Proclaim it not in the streets of Ashkelon,Or
        the daughters of the Philistines will rejoice,The daughters of the uncircumcised
        (pagans) will exult.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  O mountains of Gilboa,Let not dew or rain be upon you, nor fields
        with offerings;For there the shield of the mighty was defiled,The shield
        of Saul, [dry, cracked] not anointed with oil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'From the blood of the slain, from the fat of the mighty,The bow of
        Jonathan did not turn back,And the sword of Saul did not return empty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Saul and Jonathan, beloved and lovely and friends in their lives,And
        in their death they were not separated;They were swifter than eagles,They
        were stronger than lions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'O daughters of Israel, weep over Saul,Who clothed you luxuriously
        in scarlet,Who put ornaments of gold on your apparel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'How the mighty have fallen in the midst of the battle!Jonathan lies
        slain upon your high places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I am distressed for you, my brother Jonathan;You have been a good
        friend to me.Your love toward me was more wonderfulThan the love of women.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "How the mighty have fallen,And the weapons of war have perished!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Made King over Judah'
      title: David Made King over Judah
      number: 1
      content: "  So it happened after this that David inquired of the Lord, saying,
        \u201CShall I go up into one of the cities of Judah?\u201D And the Lord said
        to him, \u201CGo up.\u201D David asked, \u201CWhere shall I go?\u201D And
        He said, \u201CTo Hebron.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So David went up there [to Hebron] with his two wives also, Ahinoam
        of Jezreel and Abigail the widow of Nabal of Carmel [in Judah]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David brought up his men who were with him, each one with his
        household; and they lived in the cities of Hebron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the men of Judah came and there they anointed David king over
        the house of Judah.  Then they told David, \u201CIt was the men of Jabesh-gilead
        who buried Saul.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David sent messengers to the men of Jabesh-gilead, and said to
        them, \u201CMay you be blessed by the Lord because you showed this graciousness
        and loyalty to Saul your lord (king), and buried him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now may the Lord show lovingkindness and truth and faithfulness to
        you. I too will show this goodness to you, because you have done this thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Ish-bosheth Made King over Israel'
      title: Ish-bosheth Made King over Israel
      number: 7
      content: "So now, let your hands be strong and be valiant; for your lord Saul
        is dead, and also the house of Judah has anointed me king over them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now [Saul\u2019s cousin] Abner the son of Ner, commander of Saul\u2019s
        army, had taken Ish-bosheth the son of Saul and brought him over to Mahanaim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He made him king over Gilead, over the Ashurites, over Jezreel, over
        Ephraim, over Benjamin, even over all Israel [except Judah]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Ish-bosheth, Saul\u2019s son, was forty years old when he became
        king over Israel, and he reigned for two years. But the house of Judah followed
        David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Civil War'
      title: Civil War
      number: 11
      content: 'And the time that David was king in Hebron over the house of Judah
        was seven years and six months.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now Abner the son of Ner and the servants of Ish-bosheth the son
        of Saul went out from Mahanaim to Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Joab [David\u2019s nephew] the son of Zeruiah and the servants of
        David also went out and met them by the pool of Gibeon. They sat down, with
        one group on one side of the pool and the other group on the other side of
        the pool. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Abner said to Joab, \u201CLet the young men now stand and have
        a contest before us.\u201D And Joab said, \u201CLet them stand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So they stood up and went over by number, twelve for Benjamin and
        Ish-bosheth the son of Saul, and twelve of the servants of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Each one of them seized his opponent by the head and thrust his sword
        into his opponents side; so they fell down together. Therefore that place
        was called Helkath-hazzurim [that is, the Field of Sides], which is in Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'There was a very fierce battle that day, and Abner and the men of
        Israel were beaten before the servants of David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Three sons of Zeruiah [the half sister of David] were there: Joab,
        Abishai, and Asahel. Now Asahel was as light and swift-footed as one of the
        [wild] gazelles in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Asahel pursued Abner and did not turn to the right or to the left
        as he followed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Abner looked behind him and said, \u201CIs that you, Asahel?\u201D
        He answered, \u201CIt is I.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So Abner said to him, \u201CTurn to your right or to your left, and
        grab one of the young men and take his armor for yourself.\u201D But Asahel
        was not willing to turn away from pursuing Abner. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Abner repeated again, \u201CTurn away from following me. Why should
        I have to strike you to the ground? How would I be able to face Joab your
        brother [and look him in the eye]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But Asahel refused to turn away; so Abner struck him in the abdomen
        with the butt end of his spear, and the spear came out his back; and he fell
        there and died on that spot. And it came about that everyone who came to
        the place where Asahel fell and died, stood still [and reflected].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But Joab and Abishai [Asahel\u2019s brothers] pursued Abner. When
        the sun was going down, they came to the hill of Ammah, which is in front
        of Giah on the way to the wilderness of Gibeon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the sons of [the tribe of] Benjamin gathered together behind
        Abner and became one troop, and took their stand on the top of a hill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Abner called to Joab, \u201CMust the sword devour forever? Do
        you not know that it will be bitter in the end? How long [will it be] before
        you tell the people to stop pursuing their brothers?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Joab said, \u201CAs God lives, if you had not spoken, then the people
        certainly would have stopped pursuing their brothers in the morning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Joab blew the trumpet; and all the people halted and no longer
        pursued Israel, nor did they fight anymore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Abner and his men went through the Arabah (desert region) all
        that night, crossed the Jordan, went through Bithron and walked the whole
        morning and came to Mahanaim [where Ish-bosheth ruled Israel].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Joab returned from pursuing Abner; and when he had gathered all the
        people together, nineteen of David\u2019s servants were missing, besides
        Asahel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But the servants of David had struck down many of Benjamin and Abner\u2019s
        men; so that three hundred and sixty men died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: And they picked up [the body of] Asahel and buried him in the tomb
        of his father in Bethlehem. Then Joab and his men walked all night and they
        arrived in Hebron at daybreak.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The House of David Strengthened'
      title: The House of David Strengthened
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a long war between the house of Saul and the house of
        David; but David grew steadily stronger, while the house of Saul grew weaker
        and weaker [to the point of being powerless].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Sons were born to David in Hebron: his firstborn was Amnon, by Ahinoam
        of Jezreel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'his second, Chileab, by Abigail the widow of Nabal of Carmel; the
        third, Absalom the son of [his wife] Maacah, daughter of Talmai the king
        of Geshur; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'the fourth, Adonijah the son of [his wife] Haggith; the fifth, Shephatiah
        the son of [his wife] Abital; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Abner Joins David'
      title: Abner Joins David
      number: 5
      content: "and the sixth, Ithream, by David\u2019s wife Eglah. These [sons]
        were born to David in Hebron.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now while war continued between the houses of Saul and David, Abner
        was proving himself strong in the house of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now Saul had a concubine whose name was Rizpah the daughter of Aiah;
        and Ish-bosheth said to Abner, \u201CWhy have you gone in to my father\u2019s
        concubine?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Abner was very angry at the words of Ish-bosheth, and he said,
        \u201CAm I a dog\u2019s head [a despicable traitor] that belongs to Judah?
        Today I show loyalty and kindness to the house of Saul your father, to his
        brothers and his friends, by not having you handed over to David; and yet
        you charge me today with guilt concerning this woman. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'May God do so to Abner, and more also, if I do not do for David just
        as the Lord has sworn to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "to transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul, and establish the
        throne of David over Israel and Judah from Dan [in the north] to Beersheba
        [in the south].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Ish-bosheth could not say another word to Abner, because he was
        afraid of him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Abner sent messengers to David [who was] in his place [at Hebron],
        saying, \u201CWhose is the land? Make your covenant (treaty) with me, and
        behold, my hand shall be with you to bring all Israel over to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "David said, \u201CGood! I will make a covenant (treaty) with you,
        but I require one thing of you: you shall not see my face unless you first
        bring Michal, Saul\u2019s daughter, when you come to see me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So David sent messengers to Ish-bosheth, Saul\u2019s son, saying,
        \u201CGive me my wife Michal, to whom I was betrothed for [the price of]
        a hundred foreskins of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Ish-bosheth sent and took her from her husband, from Paltiel the
        son of Laish [to whom Saul had given her]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But her husband went with her, weeping continually behind her as
        far as Bahurim. Then Abner told him, \u201CGo, return.\u201D And he did so.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Abner talked with the elders (tribal leaders) of Israel, saying,
        \u201CIn times past you were seeking for David to be king over you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now then, do it [and make him king]! For the Lord has spoken of David,
        saying, \u2018By the hand of My servant David I will save My people Israel
        from the hand of the Philistines and the hand of all their enemies.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Abner also spoke to [the men of] Benjamin. Then he also went to tell
        David at Hebron everything that seemed good to Israel and to the entire house
        of Benjamin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Abner came to David at Hebron, and [brought] twenty men along
        with him. And David prepared a feast for Abner and the men with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Abner said to David, \u201CLet me stand up and go, and gather all
        Israel to my lord the king, so that they may make a covenant (treaty) with
        you, and that you may reign over all that your soul desires.\u201D So David
        sent Abner away, and he went in peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the servants of David came with Joab from a raid and brought
        a great quantity of spoil with them; but Abner was not with David at Hebron,
        because David had sent him away, and he had gone in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "When Joab and all the army that was with him arrived, they told Joab,
        \u201CAbner the son of Ner came to the king, and he has sent him away, and
        he has gone in peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Joab came to the king and said, \u201CWhat have you done? Behold,
        Abner came to you; why did you send him away, so that he is already gone? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Joab Murders Abner'
      title: Joab Murders Abner
      number: 25
      content: "You know Abner the son of Ner, that he [only] came to deceive you
        [with flattering words] and to learn of your going out and coming in, and
        to find out what you are doing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When Joab left David, he sent messengers after Abner, and they brought
        him back from the well of Sirah; but David knew nothing [about Joab\u2019s
        action]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So when Abner returned to Hebron, Joab took him aside to the middle
        of the gate to speak to him privately, and there he struck Abner in the abdomen
        so that he died, to avenge the blood of Asahel, Joab\u2019s brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Afterward, when David heard of it, he said, \u201CI and my kingdom
        are forever innocent before the Lord of the blood of Abner the son of Ner. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Let the guilt fall on the head of Joab and on all his father\u2019s
        house (family); and may there never disappear from the house of Joab one
        who suffers with a discharge or one who is a leper or one who walks with
        a crutch [being unfit for war], or one who falls by the sword, or one who
        lacks food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: David Mourns Abner'
      title: David Mourns Abner
      number: 30
      content: 'So Joab and Abishai his brother murdered Abner because he had killed
        their brother Asahel in the battle at Gibeon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then David said to Joab and to all the people with him, \u201CTear
        your clothes, put on sackcloth, and mourn before Abner.\u201D And King David
        walked behind the bier. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They buried Abner in Hebron; and the king raised his voice and wept
        at the grave of Abner, and all the people wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And the king sang a dirge (funeral song) over Abner and said,\u201CShould
        Abner [the great warrior] die as a fool dies?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Your hands were not bound, nor your feet put in fetters;As a man
        falls before the wicked, so you have fallen.\u201DAnd all the people wept
        again over him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "All the people came to urge David to eat food while it was still
        day; but David took an oath, saying, \u201CMay God do so to me, and more
        also, if I taste bread or anything else before the sun sets.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And all the people took notice of it and it pleased them, just as
        everything that the king did pleased all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So all the people and all Israel understood that day that it had
        not been the will of the king to put Abner the son of Ner to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then the king said to his servants, \u201CDo you not know that a
        prince and a great man has fallen this day in Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Today I am weak, though anointed king; these men, the sons of Zeruiah,
        are too difficult for me. May the Lord repay the evildoer [Joab] in accordance
        with his wickedness!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ish-bosheth Murdered'
      title: Ish-bosheth Murdered
      number: 1
      content: "  When Saul\u2019s son Ish-bosheth [king of Israel], heard that Abner
        had died in Hebron, he lost courage, and all Israel was horrified. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Saul\u2019s son had two men who were commanders of [raiding] bands
        [of soldiers]. One was named Baanah and the other Rechab, the sons of Rimmon
        the Beerothite of the sons (tribe) of Benjamin (for Beeroth is also considered
        part of [the tribe of] Benjamin, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the Beerothites fled to Gittaim, and have been resident aliens
        there to this day).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, had a son whose feet were crippled. He
        was five years old when the news [of the deaths] of Saul and Jonathan came
        from Jezreel. And the boy\u2019s nurse picked him up and fled; but it happened
        that while she was hurrying to flee, he fell and became lame. His name was
        Mephibosheth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, Rechab and Baanah, left and
        came to the house of Ish-bosheth in the heat of the day while he was taking
        his midday rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They came into the interior of the house as if to get wheat [for
        the soldiers], and they struck him in the stomach. Then Rechab and Baanah
        his brother escaped [unnoticed]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now when they entered the house he was lying on his bed in his bedroom.
        They [not only] struck and killed him, [but] they also beheaded him. Then
        they took his head and traveled all night by way of the Arabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They brought the head of Ish-bosheth to David at Hebron, and said
        to the king, \u201CLook, the head of Ish-bosheth the son of Saul, your enemy,
        who sought your life; thus the Lord has granted my lord the king vengeance
        this day on Saul and on his descendants.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "David replied to Rechab and Baanah his brother, the sons of Rimmon
        the Beerothite, and said to them, \u201CAs the Lord lives, who has redeemed
        my life from every adversity, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "when a man told me, \u2018Behold, Saul is dead,\u2019 thinking that
        he was bringing good news, I seized and killed him in Ziklag, to reward him
        for his news. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "How much more, when wicked men have killed a righteous and just man
        in his own house on his bed, shall I not require his blood from your hand
        and remove you from the earth?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So David commanded his young men, and they killed them and cut off
        their hands and feet and hung them beside the pool in Hebron. But they took
        Ish-bosheth\u2019s head and buried it in Hebron in the tomb of Abner [his
        relative]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David King over All Israel'
      title: David King over All Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  Then all the tribes of Israel came to David at Hebron and said,
        \u201CBehold, we are your bone and your flesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In times past, when Saul was king over us, it was you who led Israel
        out [to war] and brought Israel in [from battle]. And the Lord told you,
        \u2018You shall shepherd My people Israel and be ruler over them.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So all the elders (tribal leaders) of Israel came to the king at
        Hebron, and King David made a covenant with them at Hebron before the Lord;
        and they anointed him king over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David was thirty years old when he became king, and he reigned forty
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In Hebron he reigned over Judah seven years and six months, and in
        Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years over all Israel and Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now the king and his men went to Jerusalem against the Jebusites,
        the inhabitants of the land, who said to David, \u201CYou shall not enter
        here, for the blind and the lame [even the weakest among us] will turn you
        away\u201D; they thought, \u201CDavid cannot come in here [because the walls
        are impenetrable].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nevertheless, David captured the stronghold (fortress) of Zion, that
        is, the City of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David said on that day, \u201CWhoever strikes the Jebusites,
        let him go up through the [underground] water shaft to strike the lame and
        the blind, who are detested by David\u2019s soul [because of their arrogance].\u201D
        So [for that reason] they say, \u201CThe blind or the lame (Jebusites) shall
        not come into the [royal] house [of Israel].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So David lived in the stronghold and called it the City of David.
        And he built all around [the surrounding area] from the Millo [fortification]
        and inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'David became greater and greater, for the Lord, the God of hosts
        (armies), was with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Hiram the king of Tyre sent messengers to David with cedar trees,
        carpenters, and stonemasons; and they built a house (palace) for David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And David knew that the Lord had established him as king over Israel,
        and that He had exalted his kingdom for His people Israel\u2019s sake.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'David took more concubines and wives from Jerusalem, after he came
        from Hebron; and more sons and daughters were born to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And these are the names of those who were born to him in Jerusalem:
        Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ibhar, Elishua, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: War with the Philistines'
      title: War with the Philistines
      number: 16
      content: 'Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over
        Israel, all the Philistines went up to look for him, but he heard about it
        and went down to the stronghold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the Philistines had come and spread out [for battle] in the Valley
        of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "David inquired of the Lord, saying, \u201CShall I go up against the
        Philistines? Will You hand them over to me?\u201D And the Lord said to David,
        \u201CGo up, for I will certainly hand them over to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So David came to Baal-perazim, and he defeated them there, and said,
        \u201CThe Lord has broken through my enemies before me, like a breakthrough
        of water.\u201D So he named that place Baal-perazim (master of breakthroughs). "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The Philistines abandoned their [pagan] idols there, so David and
        his men took them away [to be burned].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The Philistines came up once again and spread out in the Valley of
        Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "When David inquired of the Lord, He said, \u201CYou shall not go
        up, but circle around behind them and come at them in front of the balsam
        trees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the balsam
        trees, then you shall pay attention and act promptly, for at that time the
        Lord will have gone out before you to strike the army of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: David did just as the Lord had commanded him, and struck down the
        Philistines from Geba as far as Gezer.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Peril in Moving the Ark'
      title: Peril in Moving the Ark
      number: 1
      content: '  Again David gathered together all the chosen men of Israel, thirty
        thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And David arose and went with all those who were with him to Baale-judah
        [Kiriath-jearim], to bring up from there [to Jerusalem] the ark of God which
        is called by the Name\u2014the very Name of the Lord of hosts, who dwells
        enthroned above the cherubim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They placed the ark of God on a new cart and brought it out of the
        house of Abinadab, which was on the hill; and Uzzah and Ahio, sons of Abinadab,
        were leading the new cart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they brought it with the ark of God from the house of Abinadab,
        which was on the hill; and Ahio was walking in front of the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Meanwhile, David and all the house of Israel were celebrating and
        dancing before the Lord with all kinds of instruments made of fir or cypress
        wood, with lyres, harps, tambourines, castanets, and cymbals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When they came to Nacon\u2019s threshing floor, Uzzah reached out
        [with his hand] to the ark of God and took hold of it, because the oxen [stumbled
        and] nearly overturned it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the anger of the Lord burned against Uzzah, and God struck him
        there for his irreverence; and he died there by the ark of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "David became angry and grieved and offended because of the Lord\u2019s
        outburst against Uzzah, and that place has been called Perez-uzzah (outburst
        against Uzzah) to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So David was afraid of the Lord that day; and he said, \u201CHow
        can the ark of the Lord come to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'David was unwilling to move the ark of the Lord into the City of
        David with him; instead he took it aside to the house of Obed-edom the Gittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Ark Is Brought to Jerusalem'
      title: The Ark Is Brought to Jerusalem
      number: 11
      content: 'So the ark of the Lord remained in the house of Obed-edom the Gittite
        for three months, and the Lord blessed Obed-edom and all his household (family).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now King David was told, \u201CThe Lord has blessed the house of
        Obed-edom and all that belongs to him, because of the ark of God.\u201D So
        David went and brought up the ark of God from the house of Obed-edom into
        the City of David with rejoicing and gladness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when those who were carrying the ark of the Lord [by its poles]
        had gone six paces, he sacrificed an ox and a fatling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And David was dancing before the Lord with great enthusiasm, and
        David was wearing a linen ephod [a priest\u2019s upper garment]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So David and all the house of Israel were bringing the ark of the
        Lord up [to the City of David] with shouts [of joy] and with the sound of
        the trumpet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then, as the ark of the Lord came into the City of David, Michal,
        Saul\u2019s daughter [David\u2019s wife], looked down from the window above
        and saw King David leaping and dancing before the Lord; and she felt contempt
        for him in her heart [because she thought him undignified].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They brought in the ark of the Lord and set it in its place inside
        the tent which David had pitched for it; and David offered burnt offerings
        and peace offerings before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When David had finished offering the burnt offerings and peace offerings,
        he blessed the people in the name of the Lord of hosts (armies), '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and distributed to all the people, the entire multitude of Israel,
        both to men and women, to each a [ring-shaped] loaf of bread, a cake of dates,
        and a cake of raisins. Then all the people departed, each to his house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then David returned to bless his household. But [his wife] Michal
        the daughter of Saul came out to meet David and said, \u201CHow glorious
        and distinguished was the king of Israel today, who uncovered himself and
        stripped [off his kingly robes] in the eyes of his servants\u2019 maids like
        one of the riffraff who shamelessly uncovers himself!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So David said to Michal, \u201CIt was before the Lord [that I did
        this], who chose me above your father and all his house, to appoint me as
        ruler over Israel, the people of the Lord. Therefore I will celebrate [in
        pure enjoyment] before the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Yet I will demean myself even more than this, and will be humbled
        (abased) in my own sight [and yours, as I please], but by the maids whom
        you mentioned, by them I shall be held in honor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Michal the daughter of Saul had no child to the day of her death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Plans to Build a Temple'
      title: David Plans to Build a Temple
      number: 1
      content: '  When King David lived in his house (palace) and the Lord had given
        him rest from all his surrounding enemies, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "the king said to Nathan the prophet, \u201CSee now, I dwell in a
        house of cedar, but the ark of God dwells within tent curtains.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Nathan said to the king, \u201CGo, do everything that is in your
        heart, for the Lord is with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But it happened that night that the word of the Lord came to Nathan,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGo and tell My servant David, \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CShould
        you be the one to build Me a house in which to dwell? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I have not dwelt in a house since the day I brought the sons
        (descendants) of Israel up from Egypt, even to this day; but I have been
        moving about in a tent, even in a tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: God\u2019s Covenant with David"
      title: "God\u2019s Covenant with David"
      number: 7
      content: "Wherever I have gone with all the Israelites, did I speak a word
        to any from the tribes of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd My people
        Israel, asking, \u2018Why have you not built Me a house of cedar?\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So now, say this to My servant David, \u2018Thus says the Lord of
        hosts, \u201CI took you from the pasture, from following the sheep, to be
        ruler over My people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I have been with you wherever you have gone, and have cut off all
        your enemies from before you; and I will make you a great name, like that
        of the great men of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will appoint a place for My people Israel and will plant them,
        so that they may live in a place of their own and not be disturbed again.
        The wicked will not afflict them again, as formerly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'even from the day that I appointed judges over My people Israel;
        and I will give you rest from all your enemies. The Lord also declares to
        you that He will make a house (royal dynasty) for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When your days are fulfilled and you lie down [in death] with your
        fathers (ancestors), I will raise up your descendant after you, who shall
        be born to you, and I will establish his kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He [is the one who] shall build a house for My Name and My Presence,
        and I will establish the throne of his kingdom forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will be his Father, and he shall be My son. When he commits iniquity
        (wrongdoing), I will discipline him with the rod of men and with the strokes
        of the sons of man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But My lovingkindness and mercy will not depart from him, as I took
        it from Saul, whom I removed from before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Your house (royal dynasty) and your kingdom will endure forever before
        Me; your throne will be established forever.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: David\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "David\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 17
      content: 'Nathan spoke to David in accordance with all these words and all
        of this vision.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then King David went in and sat [in prayer] before the Lord, and
        said, \u201CWho am I, O Lord God, and what is my house (family), that You
        have brought me this far? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Yet this was very insignificant in Your eyes, O Lord God, for You
        have spoken also of Your servant\u2019s house (royal dynasty) in the distant
        future. And this is the law and custom of man, O Lord God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'What more can David say to You? For You know (acknowledge, choose)
        Your servant, O Lord God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Because of Your word (promise), and in accordance with Your own heart,
        You have done all these great and astounding things to let Your servant know
        (understand). '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Therefore You are great, O Lord God; for there is none like You,
        and there is no God besides You, according to all that we have heard with
        our ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'What one nation on earth is like Your people Israel, whom God went
        to redeem for Himself as a people and to make a name for Himself, and to
        do great and awesome things for Yourself and for Your land, before Your people
        whom You have redeemed for Yourself from Egypt, from nations and their gods? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You established for Yourself Your people Israel as Your people forever,
        and You, O Lord, have become their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now, O Lord God, confirm forever the word [of the covenant] that
        You have spoken in regard to Your servant and his house (royal dynasty);
        and do just as You have spoken, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "so that Your Name may be magnified forever, saying, \u2018The Lord
        of hosts (armies) is God over Israel;\u2019 and may the house (royal dynasty)
        of Your servant David be established before You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For You, O Lord of hosts, God of Israel, have revealed this to Your
        servant, saying, \u2018I will build you a house (royal dynasty).\u2019 For
        that reason Your servant has found courage to pray this prayer to You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And now, O Lord God, You are God, and Your words are truth, and You
        have promised this good thing to Your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Therefore now, may it please You to bless the house (royal dynasty)
        of Your servant, so that it may continue forever before You; for You, O Lord
        God, have spoken it, and with Your blessing may the house of Your servant
        be blessed forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Triumphs"
      title: "David\u2019s Triumphs"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it came about after this that David defeated the Philistines
        and subdued (humbled) them, and he took control of Metheg-ammah [the main
        city] from the hand of the Philistines.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He defeated Moab, and measured them with a length of rope, making
        them lie down on the ground; he measured two lengths to [choose those to]
        put to death, and one full length to [choose those to] be kept alive. And
        the [surviving] Moabites became servants to David, bringing tribute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then David defeated Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah, as
        he went to restore his power at the River [Euphrates]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David captured from him 1,700 horsemen and 20,000 foot soldiers.
        David also hamstrung all the chariot horses (making them lame), but reserved
        enough of them for a hundred chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the Arameans (Syrians) of Damascus came to help Hadadezer, king
        of Zobah, David struck down 22,000 Arameans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then David put garrisons among the Arameans in Damascus, and the
        Arameans became his servants and brought tribute. The Lord helped David wherever
        he went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'David took the shields of gold that were carried by the servants
        of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And from Betah and Berothai, cities of Hadadezer, King David took
        an immense quantity of bronze.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When Toi king of Hamath heard about David\u2019s defeat of all the
        forces of Hadadezer, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Toi sent Joram his son to King David to greet and congratulate him
        for his battle and defeat of Hadadezer; for Hadadezer had been at war with
        Toi. Joram brought with him articles of silver, gold, and bronze [as gifts]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'King David also dedicated these [gifts] to the Lord, along with the
        silver and gold that he had dedicated from all the nations which he subdued: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'from Aram (Syria), Moab, the Ammonites, the Philistines, and Amalek,
        and from the spoil of Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So David made a name for himself when he returned from killing 18,000
        Arameans (Syrians) in the Valley of Salt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He put garrisons in Edom; in all Edom he put garrisons, and all the
        Edomites became servants to David. And the Lord helped him wherever he went.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So David reigned over all Israel, and continued to administer justice
        and righteousness for all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Joab the son of Zeruiah was [commander] over the army; Jehoshaphat
        the son of Ahilud was recorder (secretary); '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Zadok the son of Ahitub and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar were the
        [chief] priests, and Seraiah was the scribe; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was [head] over both the Cherethites
        and Pelethites [the king\u2019s bodyguards]; and David\u2019s sons were chief
        [confidential] advisers (officials) [to the king]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Kindness to Mephibosheth"
      title: "David\u2019s Kindness to Mephibosheth"
      number: 1
      content: "  And David said, \u201CIs there still anyone left of the house (family)
        of Saul to whom I may show kindness for Jonathan\u2019s sake?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "There was a servant of the house of Saul whose name was Ziba, so
        they called him to David. And the king said to him, \u201CAre you Ziba?\u201D
        He said, \u201CI am your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king said, \u201CIs there no longer anyone left of the house
        (family) of Saul to whom I may show the goodness and graciousness of God?\u201D
        Ziba replied to the king, \u201CThere is still a son of Jonathan, [one] whose
        feet are crippled.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So the king said to him, \u201CWhere is he?\u201D And Ziba replied
        to the king, \u201CHe is in the house of Machir the son of Ammiel, in Lo-debar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then King David sent word and had him brought from the house of Machir
        the son of Ammiel, from Lo-debar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, the son of Saul, came to David
        and fell face down and lay himself down [in respect]. David said, \u201CMephibosheth.\u201D
        And he answered, \u201CHere is your servant!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "David said to him, \u201CDo not be afraid, for I will certainly show
        you kindness for the sake of your father Jonathan, and will restore to you
        all the land of your grandfather Saul; and you shall always eat at my table.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Again Mephibosheth lay himself face down and said, \u201CWhat is
        your servant, that you would be concerned for a dead dog like me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the king summoned Ziba, Saul\u2019s servant, and said to him,
        \u201CI have given your master\u2019s grandson everything that belonged to
        Saul and to all his house (family). "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You and your sons and your servants shall cultivate the land for
        him, and you shall bring in the produce, so that your master\u2019s grandson
        may have food to eat; but Mephibosheth, your master\u2019s grandson, shall
        always eat at my table.\u201D Now Ziba had fifteen sons and twenty servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Ziba said to the king, \u201CYour servant will do according
        to everything that my lord the king commands.\u201D So Mephibosheth ate at
        David\u2019s table as one of the king\u2019s sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Mephibosheth had a young son whose name was Mica. And all who lived
        in Ziba\u2019s house were servants to Mephibosheth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Mephibosheth lived in Jerusalem, for he always ate at the king\u2019s
        table. And he was lame in both feet."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ammon and Aram Defeated'
      title: Ammon and Aram Defeated
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it happened later that [Nahash] the king of the Ammonites died,
        and his son Hanun became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then David said, \u201CI will show kindness to Hanun the son of Nahash,
        just as his father did to me.\u201D So David sent [a letter along with] some
        of his servants to console him in regard to his father\u2019s death; and
        David\u2019s servants came into the land of the Ammonites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the princes of the Ammonites [were suspicious and] said to Hanun
        their lord, \u201CDo you think that David is honoring your father because
        he has sent comforters to you? Has David not sent his servants to you in
        order to search the city, to spy it out and overthrow it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Hanun took David\u2019s servants and shaved off half their beards,
        and cut off their robes in the middle as far as their hips, and sent them
        away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When David was informed, he sent [messengers] to meet them [before
        they reached Jerusalem], for the men were greatly ashamed and humiliated.
        And the king said, \u201CStay at Jericho until your beards grow, and then
        return.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the Ammonites saw that they had become an object of hatred to
        David, they sent word and hired the Arameans (Syrians) of Beth-rehob and
        the Arameans of Zobah, 20,000 foot soldiers, and the king of Maacah with
        1,000 men, and the men of Tob with 12,000 men [to fight for them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When David heard about it, he sent Joab and the entire army, the
        strong and brave men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Ammonites came out and lined up for battle at the entrance of
        the [city] gate, but the Arameans of Zobah and Rehob and the men of Tob and
        Maacah were [stationed] by themselves in the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now when Joab saw that the battlefront was against him in front and
        in the rear, he selected some of all the choice men in Israel and set them
        in battle formation to meet the Arameans (Syrians). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But he placed the rest of the men in the hand of his brother Abishai,
        and he placed them in battle formation to meet the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Joab said [to Abishai], \u201CIf the Arameans are too strong for
        me, then you shall help me; but if the Ammonites are too strong for you,
        I will come to help you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Be courageous, and let us show ourselves courageous for the benefit
        of our people and the cities of our God. And may the Lord do what is good
        in His sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Joab and the people who were with him approached the battle against
        the Arameans, and they fled before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When the Ammonites saw that the Arameans had fled, they also fled
        before Abishai and entered the city. So Joab returned from battling against
        the Ammonites and came to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When the Arameans saw that they were defeated by Israel, they gathered
        together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Hadadezer sent word and brought out the Arameans who were beyond
        the River [Euphrates]; and they came to Helam; and Shobach the commander
        of the army of Hadadezer led them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When David was informed, he gathered all Israel together and crossed
        the Jordan, and came to Helam. Then the Arameans assembled in battle formation
        to meet David and fought against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But the Arameans fled before Israel, and David killed 700 Aramean
        charioteers and 40,000 horsemen, and struck Shobach the commander of their
        army, and he died there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: When all the kings serving Hadadezer saw that they had been defeated
        by Israel, they made peace with Israel and served them. So the Arameans (Syrians)
        were afraid to help the Ammonites anymore.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Bathsheba, David\u2019s Great Sin"
      title: "Bathsheba, David\u2019s Great Sin"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then it happened in the spring, at the time when the kings go out
        to battle, that David sent Joab and his servants with him, and all [the fighting
        men of] Israel, and they destroyed the Ammonites and besieged Rabbah. But
        David remained in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "One evening David got up from his couch and was walking on the [flat]
        roof of the king\u2019s palace, and from there he saw a woman bathing; and
        she was very beautiful in appearance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "David sent word and inquired about the woman. Someone said, \u201CIs
        this not Bathsheba, the daughter of Eliam, the wife of Uriah the Hittite?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David sent messengers and took her. When she came to him, he lay
        with her. And when she was purified from her uncleanness, she returned to
        her house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The woman conceived; and she sent word and told David, \u201CI am
        pregnant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then David sent word to Joab, saying, \u201CSend me Uriah the Hittite.\u201D
        So Joab sent Uriah to David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When Uriah came to him, David asked him how Joab was, how the people
        were doing, and how the war was progressing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David said to Uriah, \u201CGo down to your house, and wash your
        feet (spend time at home).\u201D Uriah left the king\u2019s palace, and a
        gift from the king was sent out after him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Uriah slept at the entrance of the king\u2019s palace with all
        the servants of his lord, and did not go down to his house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When they told David, \u201CUriah did not go down to his house,\u201D
        David said to Uriah, \u201CHave you not [just] come from a [long] journey?
        Why did you not go to your house?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Uriah said to David, \u201CThe ark and Israel and Judah are staying
        in huts (temporary shelters), and my lord Joab and the servants of my lord
        are camping in the open field. Should I go to my house to eat and drink and
        lie with my wife? By your life and the life of your soul, I will not do this
        thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then David said to Uriah, \u201CStay here today as well, and tomorrow
        I will let you leave.\u201D So Uriah remained in Jerusalem that day and the
        next. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now David called him [to dinner], and he ate and drank with him,
        so that he made Uriah drunk; in the evening he went out to lie on his bed
        with the servants of his lord, and [still] did not go down to his house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the morning David wrote a letter to Joab and sent it with Uriah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He wrote in the letter, \u201CPut Uriah in the front line of the
        heaviest fighting and leave him, so that he may be struck down and die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So it happened that as Joab was besieging the city, he assigned Uriah
        to the place where he knew the [enemy\u2019s] valiant men were positioned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the men of the city came out and fought against Joab, and some
        of the people among the servants of David fell; Uriah the Hittite also died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Joab sent word and informed David of all the events of the war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he commanded the messenger, \u201CWhen you have finished reporting
        all the events of the war to the king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "then if the king becomes angry and he says to you, \u2018Why did
        you go so near to the city to fight? Did you not know that they would shoot
        [arrows] from the wall? "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Who killed Abimelech the son of Jerubbesheth (Gideon)? Was it not
        a woman who threw an upper millstone on him from the wall so that he died
        at Thebez? Why did you go so near the wall?\u2019 Then you shall say, \u2018Your
        servant Uriah the Hittite is also dead.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So the messenger left, and he came and told David everything that
        Joab had sent him to report. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The messenger said to David, \u201CThe men indeed prevailed against
        us and came out to us in the field, but we were on them and pushed them as
        far as the entrance of the [city] gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the archers shot at your servants from the wall. Some of the
        king\u2019s servants are dead, and your servant Uriah the Hittite is also
        dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then David said to the messenger, \u201CTell Joab this, \u2018Do
        not let this thing disturb you, for the sword devours one [side] as well
        as another. Strengthen your battle against the city and overthrow it\u2019;
        and so encourage Joab.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When Uriah\u2019s wife [Bathsheba] heard that her husband Uriah was
        dead, she mourned for her husband. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And when the time of mourning was past, David sent word and had her
        brought to his house, and she became his wife and bore him a son. But the
        thing that David had done [with Bathsheba] was evil in the sight of the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nathan Rebukes David'
      title: Nathan Rebukes David
      number: 1
      content: "  And the Lord sent Nathan [the prophet] to David. He came and said
        to him,\u201CThere were two men in a city, one rich and the other poor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The rich man had a very large number of flocks and herds,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But the poor man had nothing but one little ewe lambWhich he had
        purchased and nourished;And it grew up together with him and his children.It
        ate his food, drank from his cup, it lay in his arms,And was like a daughter
        to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now a traveler (visitor) came to the rich man,And to avoid taking
        one from his own flock or herdTo prepare [a meal] for the traveler who had
        come to him,He took the poor man\u2019s ewe lamb and prepared it for his
        guest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then David\u2019s anger burned intensely against the man, and he
        said to Nathan, \u201CAs the Lord lives, the man who has done this deserves
        to die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He shall make restitution for the ewe lamb four times as much [as
        the lamb was worth], because he did this thing and had no compassion.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Nathan said to David, \u201CYou are the man! Thus says the Lord,
        the God of Israel, \u2018I anointed you as king over Israel, and I spared
        you from the hand of Saul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I also gave you your master\u2019s house, and put your master\u2019s
        wives into your care and under your protection, and I gave you the house
        (royal dynasty) of Israel and of Judah; and if that had been too little,
        I would have given you much more! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Why have you despised the word of the Lord by doing evil in His sight?
        You have struck down Uriah the Hittite with the sword and have taken his
        wife to be your wife. You have killed him with the sword of the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now, therefore, the sword shall never depart from your house, because
        you have despised Me and have taken the wife of Uriah the Hittite to be your
        wife.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u2018Behold, I will stir up evil against you
        from your own household; and I will take your wives before your eyes and
        give them to your companion, and he will lie with your wives in broad daylight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Indeed you did it secretly, but I will do this thing before all Israel,
        and in broad daylight.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "David said to Nathan, \u201CI have sinned against the Lord.\u201D
        And Nathan said to David, \u201CThe Lord also has allowed your sin to pass
        [without further punishment]; you shall not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Nevertheless, because by this deed you have given [a great] opportunity
        to the enemies of the Lord to blaspheme [Him], the son that is born to you
        shall certainly die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Loss of a Child'
      title: Loss of a Child
      number: 15
      content: "Then Nathan went [back] to his home.  And the Lord struck the child
        that Uriah\u2019s widow bore to David, and he was very sick. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David therefore appealed to God for the child [to be healed]; and
        David fasted and went in and lay all night on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The elders of his household stood by him [in the night] to lift him
        up from the ground, but he was unwilling [to get up] and would not eat food
        with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then it happened on the seventh day that the child died. David\u2019s
        servants were afraid to tell him that the child was dead, for they said,
        \u201CWhile the child was still alive, we spoke to him and he would not listen
        to our voices. How then can we tell him the child is dead, since he might
        harm himself [or us]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But when David saw that his servants were whispering to one another,
        he realized that the child was dead. So David said to them, \u201CIs the
        child dead?\u201D And they said, \u201CHe is dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then David got up from the ground, washed, anointed himself [with
        olive oil], changed his clothes, and went into the house of the Lord and
        worshiped. Then he came [back] to his own house, and when he asked, they
        set food before him and he ate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then his servants said to him, \u201CWhat is this thing that you
        have done? While the child was alive you fasted and wept, but when the child
        died, you got up and ate food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "David said, \u201CWhile the child was still alive, I fasted and wept;
        for I thought, \u2018Who knows, the Lord may be gracious to me and the child
        may live.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Solomon Born'
      title: Solomon Born
      number: 23
      content: "But now he is dead; why should I [continue to] fast? Can I bring
        him back again? I will go to him [when I die], but he will not return to
        me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'David comforted his wife Bathsheba, and went to her and lay with
        her; and she gave birth to a son, and David named him Solomon. And the Lord
        loved the child; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: War Again'
      title: War Again
      number: 25
      content: 'and He sent word through Nathan the prophet, and he named him Jedidiah
        (beloved of the Lord) for the sake of the Lord [who loved the child].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now Joab fought against Rabbah of the Ammonites and captured the
        royal city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Joab sent messengers to David and said, \u201CI have fought against
        Rabbah; I have even taken the city of waters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So now, assemble the rest of the men, and camp against the city and
        capture it, or I will take the city myself, and it will be named after me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So David gathered all the men together and went to Rabbah, then fought
        against it and captured it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he took the crown of their king from his head; it weighed a talent
        of gold, and [set in it was] a precious stone; and it was placed on David\u2019s
        head. And he brought the spoil out of the city in great amounts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: He also brought out the people who were there, and put them to [work
        with] the saws and sharp iron instruments and iron axes, and made them work
        at the brickkiln. And he did this to all the Ammonite cities. Then David
        and all the men returned to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amnon and Tamar'
      title: Amnon and Tamar
      number: 1
      content: '  It happened afterwards that Absalom the son of David had a beautiful
        sister whose name was Tamar, and Amnon [her half brother] the son of David
        was in love with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Amnon was so frustrated because of his [half-] sister Tamar that
        he made himself sick, for she was a virgin, and Amnon thought it impossible
        for him to do anything to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Amnon had a friend whose name was Jonadab the son of Shimeah,
        David\u2019s brother; and Jonadab was a very shrewd (cunning) man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He said to Amnon, \u201CWhy are you, the king\u2019s son, so depressed
        morning after morning? Will you not tell me?\u201D And Amnon said to him,
        \u201CI am in love with Tamar, my [half-] brother Absalom\u2019s sister.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jonadab said to him, \u201CGo to bed and pretend you are sick; and
        when your father [David] comes to see you, say to him, \u2018Just let my
        sister Tamar come and serve me food, and let her prepare it in my sight,
        so that I may see it and eat it from her hand.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Amnon lay down and pretended to be sick; and when the king came
        to see him, Amnon said to the king, \u201CPlease let my sister Tamar come
        and make me a couple of cakes in my sight, so that I may eat from her hand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then David sent word to the house for Tamar, saying, \u201CGo now
        to your brother Amnon\u2019s house, and prepare some food for him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Tamar went to her brother Amnon\u2019s house, and he was in bed.
        And she took dough and kneaded it, and made cakes in his sight, and baked
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She took the pan and dished them out before him, but he refused to
        eat. And Amnon said, \u201CHave everyone leave me.\u201D So everyone left
        him [except Tamar]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Amnon said to Tamar, \u201CBring the food into the bedroom,
        so that I may eat from your hand.\u201D So Tamar took the cakes she had made
        and brought them into the bedroom to her [half-] brother Amnon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When she brought them to him to eat, he took hold of her and said,
        \u201CCome, lie with me, my sister.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "She replied, \u201CNo, my brother! Do not violate me, for such a
        thing is not done in Israel; do not do this disgraceful thing! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As for me, how could I get rid of my shame and disgrace? And you,
        you will be considered one of the fools in Israel. So now, just speak to
        the king [about taking me as your wife], for he will not withhold me from
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But he would not listen to her; and since he was stronger than she,
        he violated her and lay with her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Amnon became extremely hateful toward her, for his hatred toward
        her was greater than the love which he had for her. And Amnon said to her,
        \u201CGet up and get out!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But she said, \u201CNo, because this wrong of sending me away is
        worse than the other that you have done to me!\u201D But he would not listen
        to her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Instead, he called his young man who was his personal servant and
        said, \u201CNow throw this woman out of my presence and bolt the door behind
        her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now Tamar was wearing a [long-sleeved] robe of various colors; for
        that is how the virgin daughters of the king dressed themselves in robes.
        Then Amnon\u2019s personal servant took her out and bolted the door behind
        her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Tamar put dust on her head [in grief] and tore the long-sleeved
        robe which she had on, and she put her hand on her head and went away crying
        out [for help].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So her brother Absalom said to her, \u201CHas your brother Amnon
        been with you? But now keep silent, my sister; he is your brother; do not
        take this matter to heart.\u201D So Tamar remained secluded in her brother
        Absalom\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now when King David heard about all these things, he was very angry
        [but failed to take any action]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But Absalom did not speak to Amnon either good or bad; for Absalom
        hated Amnon because he had violated his sister Tamar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Absalom Avenges Tamar'
      title: Absalom Avenges Tamar
      number: 23
      content: "Now it came about after two full years that Absalom had sheepshearers
        at Baal-hazor near Ephraim, and Absalom invited all the king\u2019s sons
        [to a party].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Absalom came to [his father] the king and said, \u201CBehold, your
        servant has sheepshearers; please let the king and his servants go with your
        servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But the king said to Absalom, \u201CNo, my son, we should not all
        go, for we will be a burden to you.\u201D Although Absalom [strongly] urged
        David, still he would not go, but he gave him his blessing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Absalom said, \u201CIf not, then at least let my brother Amnon
        go with us.\u201D And the king said to him, \u201CWhy should he go with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But Absalom urged him [again], and he let Amnon and all the king\u2019s
        sons go with him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now Absalom commanded his servants, \u201CNotice carefully, when
        Amnon\u2019s heart is joyous with wine, and when I say to you, \u2018Strike
        Amnon,\u2019 then kill him. Do not be afraid; have I not commanded you myself
        [and in doing so have I not taken full responsibility for his death]? Be
        courageous and brave.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So the servants of Absalom did to Amnon just as Absalom had commanded.
        Then all the king\u2019s sons got up, and every man mounted his mule and
        fled.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now it happened while they were on the way [back home], that the
        [exaggerated] report came to David, \u201CAbsalom has killed all the king\u2019s
        sons, and not one of them is left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then the king stood and tore his clothes and lay on the ground [in
        mourning]; and all his servants were standing by with their clothes torn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But Jonadab the son of Shimeah, David\u2019s brother, responded,
        \u201CDo not let my lord assume that all the king\u2019s sons have been put
        to death; for only Amnon is dead. This act of revenge has been on Absalom\u2019s
        mind since the day Amnon violated his sister Tamar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So now, do not let my lord the king take the report to heart that
        all the king\u2019s sons are dead; for Amnon alone is dead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now Absalom fled. And the young man who kept watch looked up, and
        behold, many people were coming from the road behind him by the side of the
        mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And Jonadab said to the king, \u201CLook, the king\u2019s sons are
        coming. It has turned out just as your servant said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And when he finished speaking, the king\u2019s sons came, and they
        raised their voices and wept; and the king and all his servants also wept
        very bitterly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But Absalom fled and went to [his mother\u2019s father] Talmai the
        son of Ammihud, king of Geshur. And David mourned for his son every day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So Absalom fled and went to Geshur, and was there for three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: And the heart of King David longed to go to Absalom; for he was comforted
        regarding Amnon, since he was dead.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Woman of Tekoa'
      title: The Woman of Tekoa
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Joab the son of Zeruiah knew that the king\u2019s heart longed
        for Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Joab sent word to Tekoa and had a wise woman brought from there
        and told her, \u201CPlease pretend to be a mourner, and put on mourning clothes,
        and do not anoint yourself with oil, but act like a woman who has for many
        days been in mourning for the dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then go to the king and speak to him in this way.\u201D So Joab told
        her what to say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When the woman of Tekoa spoke to the king, she bowed with her face
        to the ground and lay herself down, and said, \u201CHelp, O king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The king asked her, \u201CWhat is the matter?\u201D She said, \u201CTruly
        I am a widow; my husband is dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Your maidservant had two sons, but the two of them struggled and
        fought in the field. There was no one to separate them, so one struck the
        other and killed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now behold, the entire family has risen against your maidservant,
        and they say, \u2018Hand over the one who killed his brother, so that we
        may put him to death [to pay] for the life of his brother whom he killed
        and destroy the heir also.\u2019 By doing this they will extinguish my coal
        that is left, leaving my husband without a name or a remnant (heir) on the
        face of the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David said to the woman, \u201CGo to your home, and I will give
        orders concerning you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The woman of Tekoa said to the king, \u201CMy lord, O king, the guilt
        is on me and on my father\u2019s house, but the king and his throne are guiltless.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The king said, \u201CIf anyone speaks to you [about this matter],
        bring him to me [for judgment], and he will not touch you again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then she said, \u201CPlease let the king remember the Lord your God,
        so that the avenger of blood will not continue to destroy, otherwise they
        will destroy my son.\u201D And David said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, not a
        single hair [from the head] of your son shall fall to the ground.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the woman said, \u201CPlease let your maidservant speak one
        more word to my lord the king.\u201D He said, \u201CSpeak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The woman said, \u201CNow why have you planned such a thing against
        God\u2019s people? For in speaking this word the king is like a guilty man,
        in that the king does not bring back his banished one. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For we will certainly die and are like water that is spilled on the
        ground and cannot be gathered up again. Yet God does not [simply] take away
        life, but devises plans so that the one who is banished is not driven away
        from Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now I came to speak of this matter to my lord the king because the
        people have made me afraid. So your maidservant thought, \u2018I will just
        speak to the king; perhaps the king will do what his maidservant requests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For the king will hear and save his maidservant from the hand of
        the man who would destroy me and my son together from the inheritance of
        God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then your maidservant said, \u2018Please let the word of my lord
        the king be comforting, for my lord the king is as the angel of God to discern
        good and evil. May the Lord your God be with you.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the king answered and said to the woman, \u201CDo not hide from
        me anything that I ask you.\u201D And the woman said, \u201CLet my lord the
        king please speak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The king said, \u201CIs the hand of Joab with you in all of this?\u201D
        And the woman answered, \u201CAs your soul lives, my lord the king, no one
        can turn to the right or to the left from anything that my lord the king
        has said. Indeed, it was your servant Joab who commanded me; he put all these
        words in the mouth of your maidservant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Absalom Is Recalled'
      title: Absalom Is Recalled
      number: 20
      content: "In order to change the appearance of things [between Absalom and
        you, his father] your servant Joab did this thing. But my lord has wisdom
        like the wisdom of the angel of God, to know everything that is in the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the king said to Joab, \u201CListen, I will most certainly do
        this thing; now go, bring back the young man Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Joab bowed his face toward the ground and lay himself down and blessed
        the king. Then Joab said, \u201CToday your servant knows that I have found
        favor in your sight, my lord, O king, in that the king has done the request
        of his servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So Joab got up, went to Geshur, and brought Absalom to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "However, the king said, \u201CLet him go to his own house, and do
        not let him see my face.\u201D So Absalom went to his own house and did not
        see the king\u2019s face.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now in all Israel there was no man as handsome as Absalom, so highly
        praised [for that]; from the sole of his foot to the crown of his head there
        was no blemish in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When he cut the hair of his head (for at the end of each year he
        cut it, because its weight was heavy on him) he weighed the hair of his head
        at 200 shekels by the king\u2019s weight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'To Absalom were born three sons and one daughter whose name was Tamar;
        she was a beautiful woman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Absalom lived two full years in Jerusalem, without seeing the king\u2019s
        face. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So Absalom sent for Joab, to send him to the king, but he would not
        come to him; even when he sent again a second time, he [still] would not
        come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore Absalom said to his servants, \u201CSee, Joab\u2019s property
        is near mine, and he has barley there; go and set it on fire.\u201D So Absalom\u2019s
        servants set the field on fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Joab took action and went to Absalom at his house and said to
        him, \u201CWhy did your servants set my field on fire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Absalom answered Joab, \u201CI sent for you, saying, \u2018Come here,
        so that I may send you to the king to ask, \u201CWhy have I come [back] from
        Geshur? It would be better for me to still be there.\u201D\u2009\u2019 Now
        then, let me see the king\u2019s face, and if there is guilt in me, let him
        put me to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So Joab came to the king and told him. Then David called for Absalom,
        and he came to the king and bowed his face to the ground before the king;
        and the king kissed Absalom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Absalom\u2019s Conspiracy"
      title: "Absalom\u2019s Conspiracy"
      number: 1
      content: '  After this, Absalom provided for himself a chariot and horses,
        and fifty men as runners before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He would get up early and stand beside the road to the gate [of the
        city, where court was held]; and when any man who had a dispute came to the
        king for judgment, Absalom would call to him, \u201CFrom what city are you?\u201D
        And he would say, \u201CYour servant is from one of the tribes of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Absalom would say to him, \u201CSee, your claims are good and
        right, but there is no man appointed as the king\u2019s agent to listen to
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Moreover Absalom would say, \u201COh, that I were appointed judge
        in the land! Then every man who had a dispute could come to me and I would
        get justice for him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And whenever a man approached to bow down before him, he would put
        out his hand, take hold of him, and kiss him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'This is how Absalom dealt with everyone in Israel who came to the
        king for judgment. So Absalom stole the hearts of the men of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And after four years, Absalom said to the king, \u201CPlease let
        me go and pay my vow which I have made to the Lord at Hebron [my birthplace]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For your servant made a vow while I lived at Geshur in Aram (Syria),
        \u2018If the Lord will in fact bring me back to Jerusalem, then I will serve
        the Lord [by offering a sacrifice of thanksgiving].\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And [David] the king said to him, \u201CGo in peace.\u201D So he
        arose and went to Hebron. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Absalom sent spies throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying,
        \u201CAs soon as you hear the sound of the trumpet, you shall say, \u2018Absalom
        is king in Hebron.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then two hundred men from Jerusalem who were invited [as guests to
        his sacrificial feast] went with Absalom. They went innocently and knew nothing
        [about his plan against David]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: David Flees Jerusalem'
      title: David Flees Jerusalem
      number: 12
      content: "And Absalom sent for Ahithophel the Gilonite, David\u2019s counselor,
        from his city Giloh, while he was offering sacrifices. And the conspiracy
        grew strong, for the people with Absalom increased continually.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then a messenger came to David, saying, \u201CThe hearts of the men
        of Israel are with Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "David said to all his servants who were with him at Jerusalem, \u201CArise,
        let us flee, or none of us will escape from Absalom! Go in haste, or he will
        overtake us quickly and bring disaster on us and strike the city with the
        edge of the sword.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The king\u2019s servants said to him, \u201CListen, your servants
        are ready to do whatever my lord the king decides.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the king left, and all his household with him. But the king left
        behind ten women who were  concubines to take care of the house (palace). '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The king left, and all the people with him, and they stopped at the
        last house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "All of David\u2019s servants passed on beside him, and all the Cherethites,
        Pelethites and the Gittites, six hundred men who had come with him from Gath,
        passed on before the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the king said to Ittai the Gittite, \u201CWhy should you go
        with us, too? Go back and stay with the king [of your own country], for you
        are a foreigner and an exile as well; return to your own place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You came only yesterday, so should I make you wander with us today
        while I go where I will? Return and take your brothers back with you also.
        May lovingkindness and faithfulness be with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Ittai answered the king, \u201CAs the Lord lives, and as my lord
        the king lives, most certainly wherever my lord the king may be, whether
        for death or life, there will your servant be also.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So David said to Ittai, \u201CGo on and cross over [the Brook Kidron].\u201D
        So Ittai the Gittite crossed over with all his men and all the little ones
        who were with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'While all the country was weeping with a loud voice, all the people
        crossed over. The king also crossed the Brook Kidron, and all the people
        went on toward the way of the wilderness [that lies between Jerusalem and
        the Jordan River].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now Zadok also came, and all the Levites with him carrying the ark
        of the covenant of God. And they set down the ark of God, and Abiathar [the
        priest] came up [and officiated] until all the people had finished passing
        from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then the king told Zadok, \u201CTake the ark of God back to [its
        rightful place in] the city [of Jerusalem, the capital]. If I find favor
        in the Lord\u2019s sight, He will bring me back again and let me see both
        it and His dwelling place (habitation). "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But if He should say, \u2018I have no delight in you,\u2019 then
        here I am; let Him do to me what seems good to Him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The king also said to Zadok the priest, \u201CAre you not a seer?
        Return to the city in peace [you and Abiathar], and your two sons with you,
        your son Ahimaaz and Jonathan the son of Abiathar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "See, I am going to wait at the fords [of the Jordan] in the wilderness
        until word comes from you to inform me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So Zadok and Abiathar brought the ark of God back to Jerusalem, and
        they stayed there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And David went up the ascent of the Mount of Olives, weeping as he
        went, with his head covered and walking barefoot [in despair]. And all the
        people who were with him covered their heads and went up, weeping as they
        went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "David was told, \u201CAhithophel [your counselor] is among the conspirators
        with Absalom.\u201D David said, \u201CO Lord, I pray You, turn Ahithophel\u2019s
        counsel into foolishness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'It happened when David came to the summit [of the Mount of Olives],
        where he worshiped God, behold, Hushai the Archite came to meet him with
        his tunic torn and dust on his head [as if in mourning]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "David said to him, \u201CIf you go on with me, you will be a burden
        to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But if you return to the city, and say to Absalom, \u2018I will be
        your servant, O king; as I have been your father\u2019s servant in the past,
        so I will be your servant now;\u2019 then you can thwart (make useless) the
        advice of Ahithophel for me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Are not Zadok and Abiathar the priests with you there? So it shall
        be that every word you hear from the king\u2019s palace, you shall report
        it to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Their two sons are there with them, Ahimaaz, Zadok\u2019s son and
        Jonathan, Abiathar\u2019s son; and by them you shall send to me everything
        that you hear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So Hushai, David\u2019s friend, returned to the city, and [at about
        the same time] Absalom came into Jerusalem."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ziba, a False Servant'
      title: Ziba, a False Servant
      number: 1
      content: '  When David was a little past the summit [of the Mount of Olives],
        behold, Ziba, the servant of Mephibosheth, met him with a team of saddled
        donkeys, and on them were two hundred loaves of bread, a hundred clusters
        of raisins, a hundred summer fruits, and a jug of wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The king said to Ziba, \u201CWhy do you have these?\u201D Ziba said,
        \u201CThe donkeys are for the king\u2019s household (family) to ride on,
        the bread and summer fruit for the young men to eat, and the wine is for
        anyone to drink who becomes weary in the wilderness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CAnd where is your master\u2019s son [Mephibosheth]?\u201D
        Ziba said to the king, \u201CBehold, he remains in Jerusalem, for he said,
        \u2018Today the house of Israel will give me back the kingdom of my father.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: David Is Cursed'
      title: David Is Cursed
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king said to Ziba, \u201CBehold, everything that belonged
        to Mephibosheth is [now] yours.\u201D Ziba said, \u201CI bow down [in honor
        and gratitude]; let me find favor in your sight, O my lord the king.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When King David came to Bahurim, a man named Shimei, the son of Gera,
        came out from there. He was of the family of Saul\u2019s household and he
        was cursing continually as he came out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He threw stones at David and at all the servants of King David; yet
        all the people and all the warriors remained on his right and on his left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "This is what Shimei said as he cursed: \u201CGet out, get out, you
        man of bloodshed, you worthless and useless man! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord has returned upon you all the bloodshed of the house of
        Saul, in whose place you have reigned; and the Lord has given the kingdom
        into the hands of Absalom your son. And behold, you are caught in your own
        evil, for you are a man of bloodshed!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Abishai [David\u2019s nephew], the son of Zeruiah, said to the
        king, \u201CWhy should this dead dog (despicable person) curse my lord the
        king? Let me go over and take off his head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But the king said, \u201CWhat business is this of yours, O sons of
        Zeruiah? If Shimei is cursing because the Lord said to him, \u2018Curse David,\u2019
        then who should say, \u2018Why have you done so?\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then David said to Abishai and to all his servants, \u201CLook, my
        son [Absalom] who came from my own body, is seeking my life; how much more
        [reason] now [does] this Benjamite [have to curse me]? Let him alone and
        let him curse, for [it could be that] the Lord has told him [to do it]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Perhaps the Lord will look on the wrong done to me [by Shimei, if
        he is acting on his own]; and [in that case perhaps] the Lord will this day
        return good to me in place of his cursing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So David and his men went on the road; and Shimei went along on the
        hillside close beside David and cursed as he went and threw stones and dust
        at him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Absalom Enters Jerusalem'
      title: Absalom Enters Jerusalem
      number: 14
      content: 'The king and all the people who were with him arrived [at the Jordan
        River] weary, and he refreshed himself there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Absalom and all the people, the men of Israel, entered Jerusalem,
        and Ahithophel with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now it happened when Hushai the Archite, David\u2019s friend, came
        to Absalom, Hushai said to him, \u201CLong live the king! Long live the king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Absalom said to Hushai, \u201CIs this your loyalty to your friend?
        Why did you not go with your friend?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Hushai said to Absalom, \u201CNo! For whomever the Lord and this
        people and all the men of Israel have chosen [as king], I will be his, and
        I will remain with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Besides, whom should I serve? Should I not serve in the presence
        of David\u2019s son? As I have served in your father\u2019s presence, so
        I shall serve in your presence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Absalom said to Ahithophel, \u201CGive me your advice. What
        should we do?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201CGo in to your father\u2019s concubines,
        whom he has left behind to take care of the house; then all Israel will hear
        that you have made yourself odious to your father. Then the hands of all
        who are with you will be strengthened [by your boldness and audacity].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So they pitched a tent for Absalom on the roof [of the king\u2019s
        palace], and Absalom went in to his father\u2019s concubines in the sight
        of all Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The advice of Ahithophel, which he gave in those days, was as if
        a man had consulted the word of God; that is how all Ahithophel\u2019s counsel
        was regarded by both David and Absalom."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hushai\u2019s Counsel"
      title: "Hushai\u2019s Counsel"
      number: 1
      content: "  Then, Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201CPlease let me choose 12,000
        men, and I will set out and pursue David tonight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will strike while he is weary and exhausted, and terrify him; and
        all the people with him will flee [in terror]. Then I will attack the king
        alone, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and I will bring all the people [who follow David] back to you. The
        return of everyone depends on the [death of the] man you are seeking; then
        all the people will be at peace [and accept you as king].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the plan pleased Absalom and all the elders of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Nevertheless, Absalom said, \u201CNow call Hushai the Archite also,
        and let us hear what he has to say.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When Hushai came to Absalom, Absalom said to him, \u201CAhithophel
        has advised this [plan of action]. Should we do what he says? If not, you
        speak [and explain why not].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Hushai said to Absalom, \u201CAhithophel has not given good advice
        this time.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Hushai said, \u201CYou know your father and his men, that they
        are brave men, and they are enraged and fierce, like a bear deprived of her
        cubs in the field. Your father is a [shrewd] man of war, and will not spend
        the night with the people [knowing that you seek his life]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Behold, he has hidden himself [even] now in one of the ravines or
        in another place; and when some of your troops fall at the first attack,
        whoever hears about it will say, \u2018There has been a defeat among the
        people who follow Absalom.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And even the one who is brave, whose heart is like the heart of a
        lion, will completely lose heart and melt away; for all Israel knows that
        your father is a mighty man, and that those who are with him are brave men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But I advise that all [the men of] Israel be summoned to you, from
        Dan [in the north] to Beersheba [in the south], like the sand that is by
        the sea in abundance, and that you personally go into battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So shall we come upon David in one of the places where he can be
        found, and we will fall on him as the dew falls [unseen and unheard] on the
        ground; and of him and of all the men who are with him, not even one will
        be left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "If he retreats into a city, then all Israel shall bring ropes to
        that city, and we will drag it into the ravine until not even a pebble [of
        it] is found there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Hushai\u2019s Warning Saves David"
      title: "Hushai\u2019s Warning Saves David"
      number: 14
      content: "Then Absalom and all the men of Israel said, \u201CThe advice of
        Hushai the Archite is better than that of Ahithophel.\u201D For the Lord
        had ordained to thwart the good advice of Ahithophel, so that the Lord could
        bring disaster upon Absalom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Hushai said to Zadok and Abiathar the priests, \u201CThis is
        the advice that Ahithophel gave to Absalom and the elders of Israel, and
        this is the advice that I have given. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now then, send word quickly and tell David, \u2018Do not spend the
        night at the fords [on the west side of the Jordan] in the wilderness, but
        by all means cross over [to the east side of the river], or else the king
        and all the people with him will be destroyed [if Ahithophel is allowed by
        Absalom to lead an attack].\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now Jonathan and Ahimaaz [the priests\u2019 sons] were staying at
        En-rogel, and a maidservant [appearing to go for water] would go and tell
        them [what was happening], and they would go [secretly] and inform King David;
        for they could not [allow themselves to] be seen coming into the city [of
        Jerusalem]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But a boy saw them and told Absalom; so the two of them left quickly
        and came to the house of a man in Bahurim, who had a well in his courtyard,
        and [with his permission] they went down into it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the woman [of the house] took a covering and spread it over the
        mouth of the well and scattered grain on it; so nothing was discovered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Absalom\u2019s servants came to the woman at the house and asked,
        \u201CWhere are Ahimaaz and Jonathan?\u201D And the woman said to them, \u201CThey
        have crossed over the brook.\u201D When they searched and could not find
        them, they returned to Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "After they left, Jonathan and Ahimaaz came up out of the well and
        went and informed King David, and said to David, \u201CArise and cross over
        the Jordan River quickly, for Ahithophel has advised [an attack] against
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then David and all the people who were with him departed and crossed
        over the Jordan. By daybreak, not even one was left who had not crossed the
        Jordan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now when Ahithophel saw that his advice had not been followed, he
        saddled his donkey and set out and went to his home, to his city. Then he
        put his household in order, and hanged himself. So he died and was buried
        in the tomb of his father.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then David came to Mahanaim. And Absalom crossed over the Jordan,
        he and all the men of Israel with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Absalom put Amasa in command of the army instead of Joab. Now Amasa
        was the son of a man named Ithra the Israelite, who had married Abigail the
        daughter of Nahash, [the half sister of David and] the sister of Zeruiah,
        Joab\u2019s mother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So Israel and Absalom camped in the land of Gilead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When David came to Mahanaim, Shobi the son of Nahash from Rabbah
        of the Ammonites, and Machir the son of Ammiel from Lo-debar, and Barzillai
        the Gileadite from Rogelim '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'brought beds, basins, pottery, wheat, barley, flour, roasted grain,
        broad beans, lentils, and [other] roasted grain,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "honey, cream, sheep, and cheese of the herd, for David and the people
        who were with him, to eat; for they said, \u201CThe people are hungry and
        weary and thirsty in the wilderness.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Absalom\u2019s Death"
      title: "Absalom\u2019s Death"
      number: 1
      content: '  David numbered the men who were with him and set over them commanders
        of thousands and commanders of hundreds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then David sent the army out, a third under the command of Joab,
        a third under Abishai the son of Zeruiah, Joab\u2019s brother, and a third
        under the command of Ittai the Gittite. And the king said to the men, \u201CI
        myself will certainly go out [to fight] with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the men said, \u201CYou should not go out [to battle with us].
        For if in fact we retreat, they will not care about us; even if half of us
        die, they will not care about us. But you are worth ten thousand of us. So
        now it is better that you be ready to help us from the city [of Mahanaim].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king said to them, \u201CI will do whatever seems best to
        you.\u201D So the king stood beside the gate [of Mahanaim], and all the army
        went out in groups of hundreds and of thousands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The king commanded Joab and Abishai and Ittai, saying, \u201CDeal
        gently with the young man Absalom for my sake.\u201D And all the men heard
        when the king gave orders to all the commanders about Absalom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the men went out into the field against Israel, and the battle
        was fought in the forest of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The men of Israel [who supported Absalom] were defeated there by
        the men of David, and a great slaughter took place there that day, 20,000
        men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the battle there was spread out over the surface of the entire
        countryside, and the [hazards of the] forest devoured more men that day than
        did the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now Absalom met the servants of David. Absalom was riding on his
        mule, and the mule went under the thick branches of a massive tree, and his
        head was caught in [the thick branches of] the tree; and he was left hanging
        [in midair] between heaven and earth, while the mule that had been under
        him kept going. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "A certain man saw it and informed Joab, saying, \u201CI saw Absalom
        hanging in a tree.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Joab said to the man who informed him, \u201CYou saw him! Why then
        did you not strike him there to the ground? I would have given you ten pieces
        of silver and a belt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The man told Joab, \u201CEven if I were to feel the weight of a thousand
        pieces of silver in my hands, I would not put out my hand against the king\u2019s
        son; for we all heard the king command you, Abishai, and Ittai, saying, \u2018Protect
        the young man Absalom, for my sake.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Otherwise, if I had acted treacherously against his life (for nothing
        is hidden from the king) you yourself would have taken sides against me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Joab said, \u201CI will not waste time with you.\u201D So he took
        three spears in his hand and thrust them through the heart of Absalom while
        he was still alive [and caught] in the midst of the tree. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And ten young men, Joab\u2019s armor bearers, surrounded and struck
        Absalom and killed him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Joab blew the trumpet [to signal the end of the combat], and
        the men returned from pursuing Israel, for Joab held them back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They took [down the body of] Absalom and threw him into a deep pit
        in the forest and set up a huge mound of stones over him. Then all Israel
        fled, everyone to his own tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: David Is Grief-stricken'
      title: David Is Grief-stricken
      number: 18
      content: "Now Absalom in his lifetime had taken and set up for himself a memorial
        pillar which is in the King\u2019s Valley, for he said, \u201CI have no son
        to keep my name in remembrance.\u201D He named the memorial pillar after
        himself, and to this day it is called Absalom\u2019s Monument.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok, said, \u201CLet me run and bring the
        king news that the Lord has vindicated him by rescuing him from [the power
        of] his enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Joab told him, \u201CYou are not the man to carry news [to King
        David] today, but you shall carry news another day. On this day you shall
        carry no news, because the king\u2019s son is dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Joab said to the Cushite (Ethiopian), \u201CGo, tell the king
        what you have seen.\u201D And the Cushite bowed to Joab and ran. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said again to Joab, \u201CBut whatever
        happens, please let me also run after the Cushite.\u201D Joab said, \u201CWhy
        should you run, my son, seeing you will have no messenger\u2019s reward for
        going [because you have only bad news]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CBut whatever happens, Let me run.\u201D So Joab said to him,
        \u201CRun.\u201D Then Ahimaaz ran by the way of the plain [of the Jordan
        River] and outran the Cushite.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now David was sitting between the two gates; and the lookout went
        up to the roof of the gate by the wall, and when he raised his eyes and looked,
        he saw a man running alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The lookout called down and told the king. The king said, \u201CIf
        he is alone, he has good news to tell.\u201D And he came nearer and nearer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the lookout saw another man running, and he called to the gatekeeper
        and said, \u201CLook, another man running alone.\u201D The king said, \u201CHe
        also is bringing good news.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The lookout said, \u201CI think the man in front runs like Ahimaaz
        the son of Zadok.\u201D The king said, \u201CHe is a good man and is coming
        with good news.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Ahimaaz called out and said to the king, \u201CAll is well.\u201D
        And he bowed before the king with his face to the ground and said, \u201CBlessed
        be the Lord your God, who has handed over the men who lifted up their hands
        [to fight] against my lord the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The king asked, \u201CIs the young man Absalom safe?\u201D Ahimaaz
        answered, \u201CWhen Joab sent the king\u2019s servant, and your servant,
        I saw a great turmoil, but I do not know what it was about.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The king told him, \u201CStep aside; stand here.\u201D And he stepped
        aside and stood still.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Behold, the Cushite (Ethiopian) arrived, and said, \u201CLet my lord
        the king receive good news, for the Lord has vindicated you today by rescuing
        you from the hand (power) of all those who stood against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The king asked the Cushite, \u201CIs the young man Absalom [my son]
        safe?\u201D The Cushite replied, \u201CMay the enemies of my lord the king,
        and all those who rise against you to do evil, be [dead] like that young
        man is.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "  The king was deeply moved and went to the upper room over the gate
        and wept [in sorrow]. And this is what he said as he walked: \u201CO my son
        Absalom, my son, my son Absalom! How I wish that I had died instead of you,
        O Absalom, my son, my son!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joab Reproves David\u2019s Lament"
      title: "Joab Reproves David\u2019s Lament"
      number: 1
      content: "  It was told to Joab, \u201CBehold, the king is weeping and mourning
        for Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the victory on that day was turned into mourning for all the people,
        for the people heard it said on that day, \u201CThe king grieves for his
        son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The people stole into the city [of Mahanaim] that day, as people
        who are humiliated and ashamed steal away when they retreat in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the king covered his face and cried out with a loud voice, \u201CO
        my son Absalom, O Absalom, my son, my son!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Joab came into the house to the king and said, \u201CToday you
        have put all your servants to shame who this day have saved your life and
        the lives of your sons and your daughters, and the lives of your wives and
        concubines. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For you love those who hate you and hate those who love you. For
        you have shown today that commanders and servants are nothing to you; for
        today I know that if Absalom had lived and all the rest of us had died today,
        then you would be pleased. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: David Restored as King'
      title: David Restored as King
      number: 7
      content: "So now stand up, go out and speak kindly and encouragingly to your
        servants; for I swear by the Lord that if you do not go out, not a man will
        stay with you tonight. And this will be worse for you than all the evil that
        has come upon you from your youth until now.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king stood and sat at the gate [of Mahanaim]. And they told
        all the people, \u201CThe king is sitting at the gate,\u201D and all the
        people came before the king.  But Israel [Absalom\u2019s troops] had fled,
        every man to his tent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "All the people were quarreling throughout the tribes of Israel, saying,
        \u201CThe king rescued us from the hands of our enemies, and he saved us
        from the hands of the Philistines, but now he has fled out of the land from
        Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Absalom, whom we anointed over us, has died in battle. So now,
        why are you [leaders] doing nothing about bringing back the king?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then King David sent word to Zadok and to Abiathar the priests, saying,
        \u201CSay to the elders of Judah, \u2018Why are you the last to bring the
        king back to his house [in Jerusalem], since the word of all Israel has come
        to the king, and to his house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You are my brothers (relatives, relations); you are my bone and my
        flesh. Why then are you the last to bring back the king?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Say to Amasa [the commander of Absalom\u2019s troops], \u2018Are
        you not my bone and my flesh? May God do so to me, and more also, if you
        will not be commander of my army from now on in place of Joab.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "In this way he changed the hearts of all the men of Judah as one
        man, so they sent word to the king, \u201CReturn, you and all your servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So David returned and came to the Jordan. And [supporters from] Judah
        came to Gilgal to meet the king, to escort him across the Jordan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Shimei the son of Gera, a Benjamite of Bahurim, hurried and
        came down with the men [from the tribe] of Judah to meet King David, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and a thousand men [from the tribe] of Benjamin with him. And Ziba,
        the servant of the house of Saul, and his fifteen sons and twenty servants
        with him, rushed down to the Jordan before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then they [repeatedly] crossed the ford to bring over the king\u2019s
        household (family), and to do what pleased him. And Shimei the son of Gera
        fell down before the king as he was about to cross the Jordan, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and said to the king, \u201CLet not my lord consider me guilty, nor
        remember what your servant did wrong on the day my lord the king left Jerusalem,
        so that the king would take it to heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For your servant knows that I have sinned; therefore, behold, I have
        come today, the first of all the house of Joseph to come down to meet my
        lord the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Abishai the son of Zeruiah said, \u201CShould not Shimei be put
        to death for this, because he cursed the Lord\u2019s anointed?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "David said, \u201CWhat business is this of yours, you sons of Zeruiah,
        that you should be an adversary to me today? Should anyone be put to death
        in Israel today? For do I not know that today I am king over Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Therefore the king said to Shimei, \u201CYou shall not be put to
        death.\u201D And so the king gave him his promise.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Mephibosheth the [grand]son of Saul came down to meet the king,
        but he had not cared for his feet, nor trimmed his mustache, nor washed his
        clothes from the day the king left until the day he returned in peace and
        safety. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And when he came to Jerusalem to meet the king, the king said to
        him, \u201CWhy did you not go with me, Mephibosheth?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "He said, \u201CMy lord the king, my servant [Ziba] betrayed me; for
        I said, \u2018Saddle a donkey for me so that I may ride on it and go with
        the king,\u2019 for your servant is lame [but he took the donkeys and left
        without me]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Further, he has slandered your servant to my lord the king; but my
        lord the king is like the angel of God; so do what is good in your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For were not all of my father\u2019s household (family) nothing but
        dead men before my lord the king; yet you set your servant among those who
        ate at your own table. So what right do I still have to cry out anymore to
        the king [for help]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The king said to him, \u201CWhy speak anymore of your affairs? I
        have said, \u2018You and Ziba shall divide the land.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Mephibosheth said to the king, \u201CLet him even take it all, since
        my lord the king has returned to his own house in safety and peace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now Barzillai the Gileadite came down from Rogelim and went on to
        the Jordan with the king to escort him over the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Barzillai was a very old man, eighty years old; and he had provided
        the king with food while he stayed at Mahanaim, for he was a very great and
        wealthy man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The king said to Barzillai, \u201CCross over with me and I will provide
        for you in Jerusalem with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But Barzillai said to the king, \u201CHow much longer have I to live,
        that I should go up with the king to Jerusalem? "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'I am this day eighty years old. Can I [be useful to advise you to]
        discern between good and bad? Can your servant taste what I eat or drink?
        Can I still hear the voices of singing men and women? Why then should your
        servant be an added burden to my lord the king? '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Your servant would merely cross over the Jordan with the king. Why
        should the king compensate me with this reward? '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Please let your servant return, so that I may die in my own city
        [and be buried] by the grave of my father and mother. But here is your servant
        Chimham [my son]; let him cross over with my lord the king, and do for him
        what seems good to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "The king answered, \u201CChimham shall cross over with me, and I
        will do for him what seems good to you; and whatever you ask of me, I will
        do for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So all the people crossed over the Jordan. When the king had crossed
        over, he kissed Barzillai and blessed him, and he returned to his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Then the king went on to Gilgal, and Chimham went on with him; and
        all the people of Judah and also half the people of Israel accompanied the
        king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And all the men of Israel came to the king and said to him, \u201CWhy
        have our brothers (relatives), the men [from the tribe] of Judah, stolen
        you away and brought the king and his household and all David\u2019s men
        with him over the Jordan [instead of waiting for us to arrive]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then all the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, \u201CBecause
        the king is a close relative to us. So why then are you angry about this
        matter? Have we eaten at all at the king\u2019s expense? Or has anything
        been taken for us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then the men of Israel answered the men of Judah, \u201CWe have ten
        [tribes\u2019] shares in the king, and we have more claim on David than you.
        Why then did you treat us with contempt and ignore us [by rushing ahead]?
        Were we not the first to speak of bringing back our king?\u201D But the words
        of the men of Judah were harsher than those of the men of Israel."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Sheba\u2019s Revolt"
      title: "Sheba\u2019s Revolt"
      number: 1
      content: "  There happened to be there a worthless and wicked man named Sheba
        the son of Bichri, a Benjamite. He blew a trumpet [to call Israel to revolt]
        and said,\u201CWe have no portion in DavidAnd no inheritance in the son of
        Jesse,Every man to his tents, O Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So all the men of Israel deserted David and followed Sheba the son
        of Bichri; but the men of Judah stayed faithfully with their king, from the
        Jordan to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then David came to his house (palace) at Jerusalem, and the king
        took the ten women, his concubines whom he had left to take care of the house,
        and placed them under guard and provided for them, but did not go in to them.
        So they were confined, and lived as widows until the day of their death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now the king said to Amasa [the commander of his army], \u201CSummon
        the [fighting] men of Judah to me within three days, and be present here
        yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Amasa went to summon [the fighting men of] Judah, but he delayed
        longer than the time which David had set for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And David said to Abishai [his nephew], \u201CNow Sheba the son of
        Bichri will do us more harm than Absalom did. Take your lord\u2019s servants
        and pursue him, so that he does not find fortified cities for himself and
        escape from our sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Joab\u2019s men went after him, along with [David\u2019s bodyguards]
        the Cherethites and Pelethites and all the warriors; they went out from Jerusalem
        to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When they were at the great stone in Gibeon, Amasa came to meet them.
        Now Joab was wearing his military uniform, and over it he had a belt with
        a sheathed sword strapped around his hips; and as he went forward, it fell
        out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Amasa Murdered'
      title: Amasa Murdered
      number: 9
      content: "Joab said to Amasa, \u201CIs it going well with you, my brother?\u201D
        And with his right hand Joab took hold of Amasa by the beard [as if] to kiss
        him [in greeting].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Amasa [who had replaced Joab as David\u2019s commander] was off
        guard and not attentive to the sword in Joab\u2019s hand. So Joab struck
        Amasa in the abdomen with the sword, spilling his intestines to the ground.
        Without another blow Amasa died. Then Joab and Abishai his brother pursued
        Sheba the son of Bichri. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now one of Joab\u2019s young men stood by him and said, \u201CWhoever
        favors Joab and is for David, let him follow Joab!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Revolt Put Down'
      title: Revolt Put Down
      number: 12
      content: 'But Amasa was wallowing in his blood in the middle of the highway.
        And when the man saw that all the people who came by stopped [to look], he
        moved Amasa from the highway into the field and threw a garment over him
        when he saw that everyone who came by Amasa stopped.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When [the body of] Amasa was removed from the highway, everyone followed
        after Joab to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now Joab went through all the tribes of Israel to Abel, even Beth-maacah,
        and all the Berites; and they assembled and also went after Sheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the army of Joab came and besieged Sheba in Abel Beth-maacah,
        and they built up an assault ramp against the city, and it stood against
        the outer rampart; and all the people who were with Joab were wreaking destruction
        to make the wall fall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then a wise woman cried out from the city, \u201CHear, hear! Tell
        Joab, \u2018Come here so that I may speak to you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So when he approached her, the woman asked, \u201CAre you Joab?\u201D
        He answered, \u201CI am.\u201D Then she said to him, \u201CListen to the
        words of your maidservant.\u201D He answered, \u201CI am listening.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then she said, \u201CIn the past people used to say, \u2018They will
        certainly ask advice at Abel,\u2019 and so they settled the dispute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I am one of the peaceable and faithful in Israel. You are seeking
        to destroy a city, and a mother in Israel. Why would you swallow up (devour)
        the inheritance of the Lord?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Joab answered, \u201CFar be it, far be it from me that I would swallow
        up or destroy! "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "That is not true. But a man of the hill country of Ephraim, Sheba
        the son of Bichri by name, has lifted up his hand [in rebellion] against
        King David. Only hand him over, and I will leave the city.\u201D And the
        woman said to Joab, \u201CBehold, his head shall be thrown to you over the
        wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the woman in her wisdom went to all the people [to inform them
        of the agreement]. And they beheaded Sheba the son of Bichri and threw his
        head [down] to Joab. So he blew the trumpet [signaling the end of the attack],
        and they dispersed from the city, every man to his own tent. And Joab returned
        to Jerusalem to [David] the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now Joab was [commander] over the entire army of Israel; Benaiah
        the son of Jehoiada was [commander] over the Cherethites and Pelethites [the
        king\u2019s bodyguards]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Adoram was over the forced labor; Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was
        recorder; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Sheva was the scribe; and Zadok and Abiathar were priests; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: also Ira the Jairite was a priest to David.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Gibeonite Revenge'
      title: Gibeonite Revenge
      number: 1
      content: "  There was famine in the days of David for three consecutive years;
        and David sought the presence (face) of the Lord [asking the reason]. The
        Lord replied, \u201CIt is because of Saul and his bloody house, because he
        put the Gibeonites to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the king called the Gibeonites and spoke to them (now the Gibeonites
        were not of the sons (descendants) of Israel but of the remnant (survivors)
        of the Amorites. The Israelites had sworn [an oath] to [spare] them, but
        Saul in his zeal for the sons of Israel and Judah had sought to strike down
        the Gibeonites). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So David said to the Gibeonites, \u201CWhat should I do for you?
        How can I make it good so that you will bless the Lord\u2019s inheritance
        (Israel)?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The Gibeonites said to him, \u201CWe will not accept silver or gold
        belonging to Saul or his household (descendants); nor is it for us to put
        any man to death in Israel.\u201D David said, \u201CI will do for you whatever
        you say.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So they said to the king, \u201CThe man who consumed us and planned
        to exterminate us from remaining in any territory of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "let seven men [chosen] from his sons (descendants) be given to us
        and we will hang them before the Lord [that is, put them on display, impaled
        with broken legs and arms] in Gibeah of Saul, the chosen one of the Lord.\u201D
        And the king said, \u201CI will give them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the king spared Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, the son of
        Saul, because of the Lord\u2019s oath that was between David and Saul\u2019s
        son Jonathan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the king took the two sons of Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, whom
        she bore to Saul, Armoni and Mephibosheth, and the five sons of Merab the
        daughter of Saul, whom she had borne to Adriel the son of Barzillai the Meholathite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He handed them over to the Gibeonites, and they hanged them on the
        hill before the Lord, and the seven died together. They were put to death
        in the first days of the grain harvest, the beginning of the barley harvest
        [in the spring].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Rizpah the daughter of Aiah took sackcloth and spread it out for
        herself on the rock, from the beginning of harvest [in the spring] until
        [the autumn] rain fell on them; and she allowed neither the birds of the
        sky to rest on their bodies by day, nor the beasts of the field [to feed
        on them] by night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'David was told what Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, the concubine of
        Saul, had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then David went and took the bones of Saul and Jonathan his son from
        the men of Jabesh-gilead, who had stolen them from the open square of Beth-shan,
        where the Philistines had hanged them on the day when the Philistines had
        killed Saul in Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He brought up the bones of Saul and of Jonathan his son from there,
        and they gathered the bones of those who had been hanged [with their arms
        and legs broken]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They buried the bones of Saul and Jonathan his son in the country
        of Benjamin in Zela, in the tomb of Kish his father; and they did all that
        the king commanded. After that, God was moved by prayer for the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the Philistines were at war again with Israel. David went down
        with his servants, and as they fought against the Philistines, David became
        weary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Ishbi-benob, who was among the descendants of the giant, the
        weight of whose spear was three hundred shekels (six pounds) of bronze, was
        armed with a new sword, and he intended to kill David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But Abishai the son of Zeruiah came to David\u2019s aid, and struck
        and killed the Philistine. Then David\u2019s men swore to him, \u201CYou
        shall not go out again with us to battle, so that you do not extinguish the
        lamp of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After this, there was war again with the Philistines at Gob (Gezer).
        At that time Sibbecai the Hushathite killed Saph (Sippai), who was among
        the descendants of the giant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "There was war with the Philistines again at Gob, and Elhanan the
        son of Jaare-oregim, a Bethlehemite, killed Goliath the Gittite, whose spear
        shaft was like a weaver\u2019s beam. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'There was war at Gath again, where there was a man of great stature
        who had six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot, twenty-four in
        number; he also was a descendant of the giants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And when he taunted and defied Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimei,
        David\u2019s brother, killed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: These four [warriors] were descended from the giant in Gath, and they
        fell by the hands of David and his servants.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Psalm of Rescue"
      title: "David\u2019s Psalm of Rescue"
      number: 1
      content: '  David spoke the words of this song to the Lord when the Lord rescued
        him from the hands of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He said:\u201CThe Lord is my rock and my fortress [on the mountain]
        and my rescuer;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  My God, my rock, in whom I take refuge;My shield and the horn of
        my salvation, my stronghold and my refuge,My Savior\u2014You save me from
        violence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I call on the Lord, who is worthy to be praised,And I am saved from
        my enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the waves of death encompassed me;The torrents of destruction
        overwhelmed and terrified me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The cords of Sheol surrounded me;The snares of death confronted me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In my distress I called upon the Lord;I cried out to my God,And from
        His temple [in the heavens] He heard my voice;My cry for help came into His
        ears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the earth shook and quaked,The foundations of the heavens trembledAnd
        were shaken, because He was angry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Smoke went up out of His nostrils,And devouring fire from His mouth;Coals
        were kindled by it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He bowed the heavens also, and came downWith thick darkness under
        His feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He rode on a cherub and flew;He appeared upon the wings of the wind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He made darkness canopies around Him,A mass of waters, thick clouds
        of the skies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Out of the brightness before HimCoals of fire were set aflame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The Lord thundered from heaven,And the Most High uttered His voice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He sent out arrows and scattered them;Lightning, and confused them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The channels of the sea appeared,The foundations of the world were
        uncoveredAt the rebuke of the Lord,At the blast of the breath of His nostrils.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He sent from above, He took me;He drew me out of great waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He rescued me from my strong enemy,From those who hated me, for they
        were too mighty for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They came upon me in the day of my calamity,But the Lord was my support.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He also brought me out to an open place;He rescued me because He
        delighted in me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The Lord has dealt with me according to my righteousness;According
        to the cleanness of my hands He has rewarded me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For I have kept the ways of the Lord,And have not acted wickedly
        against my God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For all His judgments (legal decisions) were before me,And from His
        statutes I did not turn aside.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I was also blameless before Him,And kept myself from wrongdoing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Therefore the Lord has rewarded me according to my righteousness,According
        to my cleanness in His sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'With the loving and loyal You show Yourself loving and loyal,With
        the blameless You show Yourself blameless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'With the pure You show Yourself pure,With the perverted You show
        Yourself astute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And You save the afflicted people;But Your eyes are on the haughty
        whom You abase (humiliate).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For You, O Lord, are my lamp;The Lord illumines and dispels my darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For by You I can run upon a troop;By my God I can leap over a wall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'As for God, His way is blameless and perfect;The word of the Lord
        is tested.He is a shield to all those who take refuge and trust in Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For who is God, besides the Lord?And who is a rock, besides our God?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'God is my strong fortress;He sets the blameless in His way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "He makes my feet like the doe\u2019s feet [firm and swift];He sets
        me [secure and confident] on my high places.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'He trains my hands for war,So that my arms can bend (pull back) a
        bow of bronze.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'You have also given me the shield of Your salvation,And Your help
        and gentleness make me great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'You enlarge my steps under me,And my feet have not slipped.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'I pursued my enemies and destroyed them,And I did not turn back until
        they were consumed (eliminated).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'I consumed them and shattered them, so that they did not rise;They
        fell under my feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'For You have surrounded me with strength for the battle;You have
        subdued under me those who stood against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'You have also made my enemies turn their backs to me [in retreat],And
        I destroyed those who hated me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "They looked, but there was no savior for them\u2014  Even to the
        Lord [they looked], but He did not answer them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Then I beat them as [small as] the dust of the earth;I crushed and
        stamped them as the mire (dirt, mud) of the streets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'You also have rescued me from strife with my [own] people;You have
        kept me as the head of the nations.People whom I have not known served me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Foreigners pretend obedience to me;As soon as they hear [me], they
        obey me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Foreigners lose heart;They come trembling out of their strongholds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'The Lord lives, and blessed be my rock,And exalted be my God, the
        rock of my salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'It is God who executes vengeance for me,And brings down [and disciplines]
        the peoples under me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Who also brings me out from my enemies.You even lift me above those
        who rise up against me;You rescue me from the violent man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'For this I will give thanks and praise You, O Lord, among the nations;I
        will sing praises to Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "He is a tower of salvation and great deliverance to His king,And
        shows lovingkindness to His anointed,To David and his offspring forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Last Song"
      title: "David\u2019s Last Song"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the last words of David.David the son of Jesse declares,The
        man who was raised on high declares,The anointed of the God of Jacob,And
        the sweet psalmist of Israel,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThe Spirit of the Lord spoke by me,And His word was on my tongue.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The God of Israel,The Rock of Israel spoke to me,\u2018He who rules
        over men righteously,Who rules in the fear of God,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Is like the morning light when the sun rises,A morning without clouds, 
        When the fresh grass springs out of the earthThrough sunshine after rain.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Truly is not my house so [blessed] with God?For He has made an everlasting
        covenant with me,Ordered in all things, and secured.For will He not cause
        to grow and prosperAll my salvation and my every wish?Will He not make it
        grow and prosper?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But the wicked and worthless are all to be thrown away like thorns,Because
        they cannot be taken with the hand;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: His Mighty Men'
      title: His Mighty Men
      number: 7
      content: "But the man who touches themMust be armed with iron and the shaft
        of a spear,And they are utterly burned and consumed by fire in their place.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'These are the names of the mighty men (warriors) whom David had:
        Josheb-basshebeth, a Tahchemonite, chief of the captains, also called Adino
        the Eznite (spear) because of the eight hundred men killed [by him] at one
        time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Next to him was Eleazar the son of Dodo the son of Ahohi. He was
        one of the three mighty men with David when they taunted and defied the Philistines
        assembled there for battle, and the men of Israel had gone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Eleazar stood up and struck down the Philistines until his hand was
        weary and clung to the sword. The Lord brought about a great victory that
        day; the people returned after him only to take the spoil [of the slain].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Next to Eleazar was Shammah the son of Agee the Hararite. The Philistines
        were gathered into an army where there was a plot of ground full of lentils,
        and the people [of Israel] fled from the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But he took his stand in the center of the plot and defended it and
        struck down the Philistines; and the Lord brought about a great victory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then three of the thirty chief men went down and came to David at
        harvest time in the cave of Adullam, while an army of Philistines was encamped
        in the Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'David was then in the stronghold, and the garrison of the Philistines
        was then in Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And David had a craving and said, \u201COh that someone would give
        me water to drink from the well of Bethlehem, which is by the gate!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the three mighty men broke through the camp of the Philistines,
        and drew water from the well of Bethlehem by the gate, and carried and brought
        it to David. But he would not drink it, but poured it out [in worship] to
        the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201CFar be it from me, O Lord, that I should drink
        this. [Is it not the same as] the blood of the men who went at the risk of
        their lives?\u201D So he would not drink it. These things the three mighty
        men did.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now Abishai the brother of Joab the son of Zeruiah was chief of the
        thirty. He wielded his spear against three hundred men and killed them, and
        gained a reputation beside the three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He was the most honored of the thirty, so he became their commander;
        however, he did not attain to the [greatness of the] three.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man of Kabzeel,
        who had done many notable acts, killed two [famous] warriors of Moab. He
        also went down and killed a lion in the middle of a pit on a snowy day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he killed an Egyptian, an impressive and handsome man. The Egyptian
        had a spear in his hand, but Benaiah went down to him with a club, snatched
        the spear out of the Egyptian\u2019s hand and killed the man with his own
        spear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'These things Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did, and gained a reputation
        beside the three mighty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He was honored among the thirty, but he did not attain to the [greatness
        of the] three. David appointed him over his guard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Asahel the brother of Joab was one of the thirty; then Elhanan the
        son of Dodo of Bethlehem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Shammah of Harod, Elika of Harod, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh of Tekoa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Abiezer of Anathoth, Mebunnai the Hushathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai of Netophah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Heleb the son of Baanah of Netophah, Ittai the son of Ribai of Gibeah
        of the Benjamites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Benaiah of Pirathon, Hiddai of the brooks of Gaash, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Abi-albon the Arbathite, Azmaveth the Barhumite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Eliahba of Shaalbon, the sons of Jashen, Jonathan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Ararite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai the son of Maacah, Eliam the son of
        Ahithophel of Giloh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Hezro (Hezrai) of Carmel, Paarai the Arbite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Igal the son of Nathan of Zobah, Bani the Gadite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai of Beeroth, armor bearer of Joab the
        son of Zeruiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Uriah the Hittite\u2014thirty-seven in all."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Census Taken'
      title: The Census Taken
      number: 1
      content: "  Now again the anger of the Lord burned against Israel, and He incited
        David against them to say, \u201CGo, count [the people of] Israel and Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the king said to Joab the commander of the army who was with him,
        \u201CGo now through all the tribes of Israel, from Dan [in the north] to
        Beersheba [in the south], and conduct a census of the people, so that I may
        know the number of the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Joab said to the king, \u201CMay the Lord your God add to the
        people a hundred times as many as there are, and let the eyes of my lord
        the king see it; but why does my lord the king want to do this thing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Nevertheless, the king\u2019s word prevailed against Joab and the
        commanders of the army. So they went from the king\u2019s presence to take
        a census of the people of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They crossed over the Jordan and camped in Aroer, on the south side
        of the city which is in the middle of the river valley [of the Arnon] toward
        Gad, and on toward Jazer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then they came to Gilead and to the land of Tahtim-hodshi, and they
        came to Dan-jaan and around to Sidon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and they came to the stronghold of Tyre and to all the cities of
        the Hivites and Canaanites, and they went out to the south of Judah, to Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So when they had gone about through all the land [taking the census],
        they came to Jerusalem at the end of nine months and twenty days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Joab gave the sum of the census of the people to the king. In
        Israel there were 800,000 valiant men who drew the sword, and the men of
        Judah were 500,000.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But David\u2019s heart (conscience) troubled him after he had counted
        the people. David said to the Lord, \u201CI have sinned greatly in what I
        have done. But now, O Lord, please take away the sin of Your servant, for
        I have acted very foolishly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When David got up in the morning, the word of the Lord came to the
        prophet Gad, David\u2019s seer, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CGo and say to David, \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CI am giving
        you three choices; select one of them for yourself, and I will do it to you.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Gad came to David and told him, and said to him, \u201CShall seven
        years of famine come to you in your land? Or will you flee three months before
        your enemies as they pursue you? Or shall there be three days of pestilence
        (plague) in your land? Now consider this and decide what answer I shall return
        to Him who sent me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Pestilence Sent'
      title: Pestilence Sent
      number: 14
      content: "Then David said to Gad, \u201CI am in great distress. Let us fall
        into the hands of the Lord, for His mercies are great, but do not let me
        fall into the hands of man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the Lord sent a pestilence (plague) [lasting three days] upon
        Israel from the morning until the appointed time, and seventy thousand men
        of the people from Dan to Beersheba died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the [avenging] angel stretched out his hand toward Jerusalem
        to destroy it, the Lord relented from the disaster and said to the angel
        who destroyed the people, \u201CIt is enough! Now relax your hand.\u201D
        And the angel of the Lord was by the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: David Builds an Altar'
      title: David Builds an Altar
      number: 17
      content: "When David saw the angel who was striking down the people, he spoke
        to the Lord and said, \u201CBehold, I [alone] am the one who has sinned and
        done wrong; but these sheep (people of Israel), what have they done [to deserve
        this]? Please let Your hand be [only] against me and my father\u2019s house
        (family).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Gad [the prophet] came to David that day and said to him, \u201CGo
        up, set up an altar to the Lord on the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite
        [where you saw the angel].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So David went up according to Gad\u2019s word, as the Lord commanded. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Araunah looked down and saw the king and his servants crossing over
        toward him; and he went out and bowed before the king with his face toward
        the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Araunah said, \u201CWhy has my lord the king come to his servant?\u201D
        And David said, \u201CTo buy the threshing floor from you, to build an altar
        to the Lord, so that the plague may be held back from the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Araunah said to David, \u201CLet my lord the king take and offer
        up whatever seems good to him. Look, here are oxen for the burnt offering,
        and threshing sledges and the yokes of the oxen for the wood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "All of this, O king, Araunah gives to the king.\u201D And Araunah
        said to the king, \u201CMay the Lord your God be favorable to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But the king said to Araunah, \u201CNo, but I will certainly buy
        it from you for a price. I will not offer burnt offerings to the Lord my
        God which cost me nothing.\u201D So David purchased the threshing floor and
        the oxen for fifty shekels of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "David built an altar to the Lord there, and offered burnt offerings
        and peace offerings. So the Lord was moved [to compassion] by [David\u2019s]
        prayer for the land, and the plague was held back from Israel."
      comments: []
